            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.13-14_0001a" />
                
           <note type="curatorial">171-1        Aly Collection</note>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Aug 18, 6'2</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I wrote you two notes shortly after I reached home. As I did not mail them myself, I'm writing this on the off-chance that they might have been lost.</p>
                
                <p>I'm trying to get ready for the National Educational <hi rend="caps">TV</hi> show. I hope it will be all right. I wish <del/> I were burbling with enthusiasm, but no doubt I'll burble a bit when the time comes. I'm
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.37.13-14_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    
                    almost ready for my <hi rend="underline">TV</hi> course next semester.</p>
                
                <p>I hope everything is all right with you there.</p> 
                <closer>
                <salute><hi rend="underline">The same old affection</hi> &#8212; </salute>
                
                <signed>John</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript><p><hi rend="underline">Did</hi> I leave anything in that lovely bed-room?</p>
                    <closer>
                    &#8212; <signed>J.</signed>
                    </closer></postscript>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
            </div1>
            
            
